column1: Who will be elected governor of Wisconsin in 2022?
column5: ['The Democratic Party candidate', 'The Republican Party candidate', 'Someone else']

column6: Still a good bit of uncertainty in this race, but Sabato joins PredictIt in thinking this one goes red.

In terms of consensus, this is probably the most disputed election I've seen on this challenge so far. At the moment, each of the big name forecasters (Cook, Inside Elections, and Sabato) all have this rated as a tossup. The prediction markets favor Michels (R) and the polls (as modeled by 538) favor Evers. In the end, this all averages out to about 55-45, Michels, but with a large enough deviation to swing it either way. Nothing in the news at the moment is convincing me to put my thumb on the scale, so 55-45 Michels it is.
Dixon is an extremist and blue wave.
Republican now in the lead on PredictIt

This race is closer than what comes more often, but I am going to go in on the Reps taking this. They have a competitive Republican party in the state with decent candidates, and with the 7th party system forming they are becoming a more Red State.
538 assigns almost a 2/3 probability to Evers (D) winning, however I am not convinced for the following reasons and I would love some feedback @ctsats (and others)
Just using the base rate (538), one should assign a 1/3 probability to republicans, but there seems to be clear trend in their favor, hence adjusting upwards.

On further analysis, changing my odds to be more for the current governor. The presumptive Republican nominee for governor is open about banning abortion even in cases of rape and incest: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4VCjcBG4hCQ&t=74s

The crowd has this as 25/75, but I think this is more 50/50. This will no longer be a normal midterm election. Roe v. Wade being overturned will offer a boost to Democratic turnout, which will help Governor Evers. Wisconsin has a very old law on the books that is a complete ban on abortion even in cases of rape or incest, and it has just gone into effect: https://wisconsinexaminer.com/2022/06/23/republicans-leave-wisconsins-1849-abortion-ban-in-place/
President Biden is not an asset during this mid-term cycle.

wisconsin is currently marked as a toss-up state in governor races and no polling data available comparing races - historical tends to have a party in power for 8 years then flips (fairly consistently) - that methodology would indicate Evers may be reelected but his likely challenger has history as the former LtGov...
